main event: A round object with white light, the size of a pencil eraser at arm's length, was observed for 7 minutes in Bremerton, Washington on 29 January 1956. There were three separate observations of the object from 0248 to 0254, 0318 to 0319, and 0344 to 0351.
interesting points: The object was described as a round, white light, approximately the size of a pencil eraser at arm's length.
The observation lasted for 7 minutes, and there were multiple sightings of the object at different time intervals.
The report suggests that it was a probable aircraft sighting, and there were two jet aircraft recovering at McChord and one taking off, which may have been mistaken for the observed object.
No photographs were included in the report.
The observer was a warehouseman at the Navy Yard in Bremerton, Washington.
